name: Albert Park Community Orchard
short_description: Heritage fruit trees in the heart of town.
description: Public access apple and pear trees located near the roller rink and lake area of this historic park.

name: Stewart Park Deer Park Walnuts
short_description: Mature nut trees in Captain Cook's birthplace.
description: Scattered walnut and sweet chestnut trees can be found along the wooded paths near the animal enclosures.

name: Tees Estuary Sea Samphire
description: Marsh samphire and sea aster thrive on the muddy tidal banks near Saltholme and North Gare.

name: Incredible Edible Middlesbrough - Town Hall
short_description: Urban planters in the Civic Square.
description: Community planters featuring hardy herbs, kale, and pollinator-friendly edible flowers.

name: Fairy Dell Wild Garlic
description: This hidden beck-side woodland is famous for its spring covering of ramsons (wild garlic).

name: Maze Park Blackberries
description: Massive bramble thickets line the riverside paths of this nature reserve near the Tees Barrage.

name: Thorntree Hub Orchard
description: A local project providing community access to apples and plums on public green space.

name: Newham Grange Hazelnuts
description: Wild hazel trees line the public bridalways and paths surrounding the Newham Grange Farm area.

name: Ormesby Hall Sloes
description: Public footpaths bordering the National Trust estate are rich in blackthorn bushes for sloe picking.

name: Linthorpe Cemetery Elder
description: This green lung of the city acts as a nature reserve with abundant elder bushes for flowers and berries.

name: Middlehaven Edible Planters
description: Regeneration area featuring street planters with rosemary, chives, and occasional strawberry plants.

name: Redcar Coast Sea Kale
description: Wild Sea Kale and Sea Beet can be found on the shingle beaches just south of South Gare.

name: Stainsby Wood Rosehips
description: Wild rosehips and haws are plentiful along the wooded fringes of the Stainsby Beck area.

name: Flatts Lane Rosehips & Haws
description: The country park offers excellent hedgerow foraging for berries as you climb toward Eston Nab.

name: Bluebell Beck Wild Greens
description: Find wild sorrel and meadowsweet in the damp meadows surrounding the beck.
